    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix dft972 function behavior with proper alignment and normalization\n\n### Summary\nThe dft972 function in the OpenAirInterface PHY library was exhibiting unexpected behavior when called, producing incorrect FFT results or crashing in certain environments. This issue was traced to two main problems:\n\n1. Missing 32-byte alignment attributes on the twiddle factor arrays for large FFT sizes (972, 1080, 1296 points), causing SIMD operations to access misaligned memory\n2. Incorrect normalization factor indexing that used a fixed lookup table entry instead of computing the proper normalization for each FFT size\n\nThe first issue caused undefined behavior during SIMD operations, while the second led to mathematically incorrect output scaling.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts.c`: Added `__attribute__((aligned(32)))` to twiddle factor arrays for dft972, dft1080, and dft1296\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts.c`: Replaced hardcoded `dft_norm_table[14]` lookups with computed normalization factors for large FFTs\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts.c`: Fixed similar issues in dft540, dft576, dft648, dft900, and dft360 functions\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the original issue:\n1. Call the dft972 function with any input data on a system where memory alignment is strictly enforced\n2. Observe incorrect output values or segmentation faults\n3. The function may work inconsistently across different hardware platforms due to the alignment issue\n\nAfter applying this fix, the dft972 function produces mathematically correct FFT outputs with proper normalization scaling.\n"
}